# Security headers and CSP for all paths are injected by
# functions/_middleware.js (withSecurityHeaders helper). The previous /*
# catch-all here corrupted CF Pages internal 3xx redirects to 200, and the
# same engine path flattens function 4xx responses to 200 + text/html.
# Per-path Cache-Control and CORS rules below are safe and stay.

# ==============================================
# Cache-Control rules
# ==============================================
#
# Strategy (per PSI mobile audit 2026-05-14 — TTFB was the only orange field
# metric at 0.8s):
#   max-age=0          — browser always revalidates on refresh (no stale content
#                        on F5 / next-page nav)
#   s-maxage=3600      — CF edge caches HTML for 1 hour
#   stale-while-revalidate=86400 — edge serves stale up to 24h while it refreshes
#                        in the background (cheap protection against deploy gaps)
#
# CF Pages auto-purges the edge cache for the project on every successful build,
# so deploys propagate within seconds regardless of s-maxage.
#
# Applied to: static content pages (Astro static-built HTML, identical for every
# visitor). Auth-gated pages (/account, /ask, /login, /signup) deliberately omit
# this rule — the middleware adds session-aware redirects that shouldn't cache.

# Library article pages
/library/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, s-maxage=3600, stale-while-revalidate=86400

/linkinbio
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, s-maxage=3600, stale-while-revalidate=86400

